+- For 002K: seed only guarded local/dev demo staff users using existing catalogue rows. Follow 002EYA's predictable-user safety pattern (`SFPCL_DEBUG=true` plus an explicit demo seed flag), keep demo users separate from E2E users, keep reruns idempotent, seed real backend users/memberships only, and prove login + `/auth/me/` for system-admin, tracer-only, and zero-permission users without adding auth bypasses or broad permission aliases. Use the 002J harness for `/auth/me`, admin permission-denial, and any list/pagination response checks. If required catalogue roles/teams are absent, fail clearly or run the existing catalogue seed; do not create ad hoc roles/permissions.
 
