 | A-015 | Admin user list/detail read is gated by `users.user.read` OR any write user-admin permission (`users.user.create`/`update`/`disable`). §19 maps `/settings/users` to `users.user.read`, but the seeded `system_admin` role (`catalogue.py`) holds create/update/disable and NOT `users.user.read`, so a read-only gate would lock the platform's only seeded user-admin out of the screens it must operate. | Preserve current `system_admin` read access (slice 002G2 req 2/5) without inventing a new `users.user.read` seed grant for `system_admin` — that would be a source-doc change (§15.12 lists System Administrator key permissions without `users.user.read`). Write actions stay gated by their specific §12.1 permission. | `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §12.1, §15.12, §19; `sfpcl_credit/identity/catalogue.py`; `sfpcl_credit/identity/modules/admin_users.py` | 002G2-admin-user-action-permission-granularity | Medium | No | 2026-07-04 | If source docs later add `users.user.read` to the System Administrator grant (or a dedicated read-only user-admin role), tighten `READ_USERS_PERMISSION_CODES` to `{users.user.read}` and update the seed + tests. |
+| A-016 | The 002J API contract harness asserts the `available_actions` object-item target shape only against an internal sample. Current `/api/v1/auth/me/` keeps returning a flat list of canonical permission-code strings that mirrors `permissions`. | The selected slice explicitly says §44's object item shape is the target contract, while verified current `/auth/me/` output is flat strings; changing `/auth/me/` would be a public API change outside this harness slice. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §44; `docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md` current-user response; `docs/slices/002J-api-contract-test-harness.md` | 002J-api-contract-test-harness and future detail endpoint slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-04 | Future detail endpoints should return §44 object-shaped `available_actions`; a later reconciliation slice may decide whether `/auth/me/` also moves from flat strings to objects or remains a compatibility permission list. |
