+| A-016 | The 002J API contract harness asserts the `available_actions` object-item target shape only against an internal sample. Current `/api/v1/auth/me/` keeps returning a flat list of canonical permission-code strings that mirrors `permissions`. | The selected slice explicitly says §44's object item shape is the target contract, while verified current `/auth/me/` output is flat strings; changing `/auth/me/` would be a public API change outside this harness slice. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §44; `docs/working/API_CONTRACTS.md` current-user response; `docs/slices/002J-api-contract-test-harness.md` | 002J-api-contract-test-harness and future detail endpoint slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-04 | Future detail endpoints should return §44 object-shaped `available_actions`; a later reconciliation slice may decide whether `/auth/me/` also moves from flat strings to objects or remains a compatibility permission list. |
